pve-modkit (0.1.0) trixie; urgency=low

  * Initial release.
    - Unified `pve-modkit` Perl CLI (subcommands: patch tpl, patch pveproxy,
      index, sync, enable, disable, list/status, unpatch, help).
    - Template patch: idempotent injection of the modkit loader <script> into
      /usr/share/pve-manager/index.html.tpl. Spliced textually and gated by a
      Template Toolkit render check (the template is not valid HTML), with
      backup + restore-on-failure and --remove.
    - pveproxy patch: registers the /modkit/ static dir key in
      PVE/Service/pveproxy.pm via a PPI-located anchor, gated by `perl -c`,
      with backup + restore-on-failure. Exit 10 signals the maintainer scripts
      to fully restart pveproxy (a reload will not rebuild its $dirs table).
    - Mods are self-contained dirs under /usr/share/pve-modkit/mods/ served at
      /modkit/{mod}/{entry}; the loader (ext.js) fetches the enabled-only
      /modkit/index.json manifest and injects each mod on page load.
    - systemd pve-modkit.path watcher runs `pve-modkit sync` on mod add/remove,
      regenerating the manifest and restarting pveproxy only when the served
      route set changed.
    - dpkg triggers (interest-noawait /usr/share/pve-manager and
      /usr/share/perl5/PVE) re-apply both idempotent patches on pve-manager /
      PVE upgrades.
    - Ships one subtle default mod (modkit-active-badge): a "modkit: active"
      badge beside the PVE version header. Fuller demo mods live in the source
      tree under examples/ and are not installed.

 -- Mark S. <the@wondersmith.dev>  Fri, 17 Jul 2026 21:52:44 -0400
